step_data.thought:
I'm now on the Export page of OpenStreetMap, which is perfect for my task of finding alternative download sources. Looking at the page content, I can see that there's already a section listing alternative download sources below the main export functionality. The page has a description list with several alternative sources listed:

1. Overpass API - for downloading a specific bounding box from a mirror of the OpenStreetMap database
2. Planet OSM - for regularly-updated copies of the complete OpenStreetMap database
3. Geofabrik Downloads - for regularly-updated extracts of continents, countries, and selected cities
4. Other Sources - which links to additional sources listed on the OpenStreetMap Wiki

These are exactly the alternative download sources I was looking for. I should inform the user about these options.
step_data.action:
stop('I found several alternative download sources for OpenStreetMap data:

1. Overpass API - For downloading specific bounding boxes from a mirror of the OpenStreetMap database
2. Planet OSM - Provides regularly-updated copies of the complete OpenStreetMap database
3. Geofabrik Downloads - Offers regularly-updated extracts of continents, countries, and selected cities
4. Other Sources - The OpenStreetMap Wiki lists additional download options

These alternatives are available on the Export page of OpenStreetMap and provide different options depending on your specific needs.')
